# StudyBuddyAI — UI Theme

## When to use
Invoke `@theme` (or follow these rules automatically) for any change to:
- `ui/templates/**/*.html`
- `ui/static/css/**`
- `tailwind.config.js`
- Inline styles, new components, or layout changes

## Design intent
Cozy study-room aesthetic: warm yellows, browns, and cream. Friendly, readable, mobile-first. Mascot: Avner the capybara.

## Color palette (Tailwind tokens — do not hardcode hex in templates)

| Token | Hex | Use |
|-------|-----|-----|
| `warm-beige` | `#FFF8E6` | Page background, PWA theme-color |
| `cream` / `soft-cream` | `#FAF3D7` / `#FFFAF0` | Cards, secondary surfaces |
| `warm-yellow` / `golden-yellow` / `butter-yellow` | `#F7D774` / `#F2C94C` / `#FFEAA7` | Accents, CTAs, focus rings |
| `cozy-brown` / `caramel` / `coffee` | `#8B5E34` / `#A47148` / `#6F4E37` | Navbar, primary buttons |
| `dark-brown` | `#4B2E16` | Body text, headings |
| `warm-gray` / `light-brown` | `#BFA585` / `#D4A574` | Borders, muted text |
| `success` / `warning` / `error` / `info` | warm greens/ambers | Status only |

Legacy aliases (`hoodie-orange`, `navbar-dark`, `teal`) exist for compatibility — prefer the cozy-brown / golden-yellow names in new code.

In `input.css`, reference colors via `theme('colors.<token>')` inside `@layer` blocks.

## Typography
- Font stack: `Inter`, `Assistant`, system sans-serif (`font-sans` in Tailwind).
- Hebrew RTL is default; English LTR when `current_locale == 'en'` (see `base.html`).

## Layout patterns
- Mobile-first; breakpoint `769px` for desktop background swap.
- Sticky navbar: `bg-cozy-brown shadow-warm-lg`.
- Cards: rounded (`rounded-xl` / `rounded-2xl`), `shadow-soft` or `shadow-warm`, hover lift where siblings use it.
- Min touch target: 48px on interactive elements.

## CSS structure
1. **Source**: edit `ui/static/css/input.css` (Tailwind layers + custom components).
2. **Build**: compile to `ui/static/css/styles.css` via Tailwind (`package.json` / project build script).
3. **Do not** add one-off hex colors in templates — use Tailwind utility classes from the palette above.

## Reuse before inventing
Before adding new UI classes, check `input.css` `@layer components` for existing patterns: `.btn-primary`, `.btn-secondary`, `.card`, `.form-input`, alert variants, HTMX indicators.

## Accessibility
- `focus-visible` outline: `golden-yellow` (already in `input.css`).
- ARIA labels on icon-only buttons.
- Sufficient contrast: dark-brown text on cream/warm-beige backgrounds.

## Do not
- Introduce cool blues, grays, or generic Bootstrap-style palettes.
- Use raw `#hex` in HTML `class` attributes when a Tailwind token exists.
- Break RTL layout (test with Hebrew `dir="rtl"`).
- Add new CSS frameworks — Tailwind + existing `input.css` only.
